License & provenance
--------------------
The upstream `dolthub/sqllogictest` repository describes itself as an
"unofficial mirror" of the SQLite consortium's sqllogictest corpus
(see its README). The original SQLite consortium sqllogictest material
is in the public domain
(https://www.sqlite.org/sqllogictest/doc/trunk/about.wiki). The Dolt
mirror's parser/runner Go code is MIT-licensed in the typical Dolt
project convention; the test corpus files (this one included) are
treated by the Dolt project as the public-domain SQLite-derived
fixtures they originally were.

sluice itself is licensed under Apache-2.0
(see the top-level LICENSE file at the repo root). Apache-2.0 is
compatible with both MIT and public-domain inclusions; vendoring this
fixture for use in sluice's test suite poses no licensing conflict.

Why vendored (not git submodule)
--------------------------------
A vendored copy gives reproducible test runs without a submodule init
step in fresh clones. The trade-off is that updates to the upstream
file require a manual refresh: re-fetch the file from the URL above,
update the "Repo SHA" / "File SHA" / "Vendored on" / "Size" entries in
this NOTICE, and verify the test still passes against the new corpus.

Test consumer
-------------
  internal/translate/ddl_fixture_test.go  (build tag: integration ddlfixture)

The test runs only when both `integration` and `ddlfixture` build
tags are set, so default `go test ./...` and the default CI
`Integration` job don't pay the testcontainer + fixture cost. See
that file's package comment for the operator-facing run instructions.
